{"word":"Τριβαλλοί","slug":"Τριβαλλοί","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n104816\" key=\"*triballoi/\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Τρῐβαλλοί</orth> (on the accent, <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> Hdn.Gr.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0061.tlg002:1:158\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.158</biblScope> </bibl>), <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">οἱ</gen>, <sense id=\"n104816.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the Triballi,</tr_> a people on the borders of Thrace (v. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:49\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.49</biblScope> </bibl>): hence as a Comic name for barbarian gods, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg006.perseus-grc1:1529\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Av.\">Av.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1529</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg006.perseus-grc1:1533\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1533</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg006.perseus-grc1:1627\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1627</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ούδ᾽ ἐν Τριβαλλοῖς ταῦτά γ᾽ ἐστὶν ἔννομα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0402.tlg001:241\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alex.\">Alex.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">241</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">καὶ ποὺ μὲν καλὸν τὸν πατέρα θύειν, οἷον ἐν</foreign> T. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg044:115b:23\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Top.\">Top.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">115b23</biblScope> </bibl>:—<pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adj.\">Adj.</a></pos> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Τρῐβαλλικός</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ή</itype>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">όν</itype>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:49\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.49</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n104816.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> a slang term for <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">young fellows who lounge about taverns,</tr_> etc., <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> the 'Mohocks' of Addison's time, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0014.tlg054.perseus-grc1:39\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.\">D.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">54.39</biblScope> </bibl>:—hence the Comic exaggeration <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Τρῐβαλλο-ποπᾰνό-θρεπτα</orth> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μειρακύλλια,</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">tavern-bred Mohocks,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0458.tlg001:75:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eub.\">Eub.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">75.3</biblScope> </bibl> (Casaubon for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Τριβαλλο-πανό-θρεπτα</foreign>: Meineke suggests <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Τριβαλλο-μαμμό-θρεπτα,</foreign> and Kock defends the Ms. reading).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}